<heading id="D0A196454B11FF9F14F9D58FFD28FB1F" box="[136,712,1238,1265]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB4606074B11FF9F14F9D58FFD28FB1F" box="[136,712,1238,1265]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
<treatmentCitation id="0AF707384B11FF9F14F9D58FFD28FB1F" author="Carriere, E. A." box="[136,712,1238,1265]" page=")" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" year="1866">
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F14F9D58FFD28FB1F" authority="de Lannoy ex Carriere (1866: 106)" authorityName="de Lannoy ex Carriere, P" authorityPageNumber="106" authorityYear="1866" box="[136,712,1238,1265]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F14F9D58FFEDCFB1F" bold="true" box="[136,316,1238,1265]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Abies numidica</emphasis>
de Lannoy ex 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F1593D58FFD28FB1F" author="Carriere, E. A." box="[482,712,1238,1265]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="106 - 107" refId="ref7891" refString="Carriere, E. A. (1866) Abies numidina. Revue Horticole (Paris) 37: 106 - 107. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 196547  page / 132 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1866">Carrière (1866: 106)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34C72A24B11FF9F14F9D447FE5BF80B" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE921294B11FF9F14F9D447FE10FA26" blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F152FD447FD1FFAD7" authority="(Carriere 1866: 106)" baseAuthorityName="Carriere" baseAuthorityPageNumber="106" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[350,767,1310,1337]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F152FD447FDEDFAD6" box="[350,525,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Abies numidica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F166CD447FD17FAD7" author="Carriere, E. A." box="[541,759,1310,1337]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" pagination="106 - 107" refId="ref7891" refString="Carriere, E. A. (1866) Abies numidina. Revue Horticole (Paris) 37: 106 - 107. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 196547  page / 132 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1866">Carrière 1866: 106</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
includes a complete and extensive description of this plant, a diagnosis to differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F166BD41AFD74FAB2" authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[538,660,1347,1373]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinsapo">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F166BD41AFD74FAB2" box="[538,660,1347,1373]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">A. pinsapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and several comments about the locality: “confinée dans la Kabylie algérienne, cette ancienne province à laquelle les Romains avaient donné le nom de 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F10F3D43FFB01FA6E" box="[1154,1249,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Numidie</emphasis>
. Elle habite tout particulièrement les monts Tababor et Grand-Babor, à une altitude assez élevée pour que, dans certains endroits, la neige soit presque permanente”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B11FF9F14CCD48BFE66F9DA" blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">The protologue also includes relevant comments referring to the studied gatherings: “A plusieurs reprises, il a eu l’obligeance de m’envoyer des échantillons à divers états de cette espèce, et c’est d’après ceux-ci que j’ai fait la description ci-dessus”.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B11FF9F14CCD767FC72F8BA" blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
<materialsCitation id="3B3E2B744B11FF9F14CCD767FC6EF8BA" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3801076302" collectorName="M. Delannoy" location="Mt Tababor Kabylie province" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Constantine" typeStatus="syntype">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F14CCD767FE75F9B6" author="Farjon, A." box="[189,405,1598,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref8781" refString="Farjon, A. (2010) A handbook of the world's conifers, vol. 1. Brill Academic Publishers, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1111 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789047430629" type="book" year="2010">Farjon (2010: 108)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned “Type not designated”. We have located a specimen relevant at P, with barcode P00507232. This specimen bears a stem well preserved, with leaves, and a label annotated as “Herb. Mus. Paris. / 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F14F9D7DFFE4CF94E" authority="Delannoy" authorityName="de Lannoy ex Carriere, P" authorityYear="1866" box="[136,428,1670,1696]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">Abies numidica Delannoy</taxonomicName>
/ 
<location id="8E8977F24B11FF9F15B3D7DEFCE9F94E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FF903F4B11FF9F14F9D58FFE5BF80B:8E8977F24B11FF9F15B3D7DEFCE9F94E" box="[450,777,1670,1697]" name="Mt Tababor Kabylie province" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" stateProvince="Constantine">
<superScript id="7C238C614B11FF9F15B3D7DEFE00F97A" attach="left" box="[450,480,1670,1697]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Mt</superScript>
Tababor Kabylie province
</location>
/ In 
<collectingRegion id="4992EFCB4B11FF9F174CD7DFFC23F94E" box="[829,963,1670,1696]" country="Algeria" name="Constantine" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Constantine</collectingRegion>
/ Donné par 
<collectorName id="26A344FF4B11FF9F1024D7DEFB0CF94E" box="[1109,1260,1670,1697]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">M. Delannoy</collectorName>
” (
<figureCitation id="136D3DAC4B11FF9F1175D7DFFAA8F94F" box="[1284,1352,1670,1697]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[274,1314,190,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-20@12.[274,1314,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Lectotype of Abies numidica de Lannoy ex Carrière, P (barcode P00507232). Photography courtesy of Herbarium P; reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605324/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Maybe this specimen could be treated as a “ 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B11FF9F1666D7F3FD96F92A" box="[535,630,1706,1732]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">syntype</typeStatus>
”. However, it is clearly relevant that the specimen lacks any annotation by Carrière that undoubtedly links it to the material mentioned by Carrière in the prologue. The specimen does not have the collection date. In addition, there is also no evidence or any link to consider the specimen at P as part of the material sent by Lannoy to Carrière before the publication of the protologue. Therefore, unfortunately, this material cannot be indubitably considered as original material according to 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F1771D662FCCFF8BB" box="[768,815,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">ICN</emphasis>
Art. 9.4
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B11FF9F14CCD606FE5BF80B" blockId="10.[136,1452,1310,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
<materialsCitation id="3B3E2B744B11FF9F14CCD606FE57F80B" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3801076301" collectorName="Lannoy" county="Kabylie" location="Alizoti" municipality="Tababor" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Constantine" typeStatus="neotype">
However, the specimen P00507232 is the only material that we have found collected by 
<collectorName id="26A344FF4B11FF9F10D3D606FB18F897" box="[1186,1272,1887,1913]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Lannoy</collectorName>
in the localities cited in the protologue (
<collectingRegion id="4992EFCB4B11FF9F15ECD6DBFDC7F872" box="[413,551,1922,1948]" country="Algeria" name="Constantine" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Constantine</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCounty id="628859A54B11FF9F1644D6DBFD70F872" box="[565,656,1922,1948]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Kabylie</collectingCounty>
, 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B8DBB534B11FF9F16EFD6DBFD1FF873" box="[670,767,1922,1949]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Tababor</collectingMunicipality>
). The specimen is well preserved and clearly represents the traditional concept and current application of 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B11FF9F16F5D6FEFCEAF82E" authorityName="de Lannoy ex Carriere, P" authorityYear="1866" box="[644,778,1958,1985]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F16F5D6FEFD75F82F" box="[644,661,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F16D3D6FFFCEAF82E" box="[674,778,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">numidica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<location id="8E8977F24B11FF9F1769D6FFFC88F82E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03FF903F4B11FF9F14F9D58FFE5BF80B:8E8977F24B11FF9F1769D6FFFC88F82E" box="[792,872,1958,1984]" county="Kabylie" municipality="Tababor" name="Alizoti" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" stateProvince="Constantine">Alizoti</location>
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B11FF9F171FD6FEFC46F82E" box="[878,934,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
201, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B11FF9F1792D6FFFB8FF82E" author="Farjon, A." box="[995,1135,1958,1984]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refId="ref8820" refString="Farjon, A. (2017) A handbook of the world's conifers, 2 nd ed., vol. 1. Brill Academic Publishers, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1153 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004324510" type="book" year="2017">Farjon 2017</bibRefCitation>
). This material is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B11FF9F14A1D692FEC9F80B" box="[208,297,1995,2021]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">neotype</typeStatus>
of the name
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
